==Post-match==
[[File:Chelsea 2 Spurs 0 - the Wembley arch is blue (16507321159).jpg|thumb|The arch of Wembley Stadium was illuminated in blue after Chelsea's victory.]]
Mourinho was pleased to have won the final, earning the 21st trophy of his managerial career: "I am like a kid winning the first one, it's hard for me to live without titles. I need to feed myself with them."<ref name=moureaction>{{cite news|title=Chelsea: Jose Mourinho seeks more trophies after League Cup|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/31688077|accessdate=2 March 2015|work=BBC Sport|date=1 March 2015}}</ref> Terry was optimistic about the club's prospects for the future, saying "It is the start of something...we've got a great squad, with some great young players, and hungry and experienced players too. It's a great mix."<ref name=moureaction/> Although praising the atmosphere at Wembley, Terry ruled out returning to the [[England national football team|England team]], for whom he had not played since 2012.<ref>{{cite news|title=John Terry: Chelsea captain rules out an England return|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/31692530|accessdate=2 March 2015|work=BBC Sport|date=2 March 2015}}</ref> Despite losing, Pochettino expressed pride in his team's performance.<ref>{{cite news|title=Chelsea 2-0 Tottenham: Pochettino 'proud' of Spurs performance|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/31687416|accessdate=2 March 2015|work=BBC Sport|date=1 March 2015}}</ref>

Mati<U+0107> took part in Chelsea's trophy ceremony in full kit despite being suspended, similar to what Terry had done after Chelsea won the [[2012 UEFA Champions League Final]] with him suspended.<ref name=matic>{{cite news|title=Matic<U+2019>s kit, phone calls, but no party: Chelsea's cup celebrations|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/31687889|accessdate=2 March 2015|work=BBC Sport|date=1 March 2015}}</ref> Mourinho did not concur with the official [[man of the match]] award going to Terry, stating that the honour should have gone to [[Thibaut Courtois]] and [[Filipe Lu<U+00ED>s]] for their performances against Liverpool, and [[Andreas Christensen]] for his performance against Shrewsbury Town.<ref name=matic/>

